import React from 'react'
import {BrowserRouter as Router, Routes, Route} from "react-router-dom";
import LoginUser from './Pages/Users/LoginUser'
import LoginManager from "./Pages/Manager/LoginManager"
import ManagerDashboard from './Pages/Users/ManagerDashboard'
import HomeManager from './Pages/Users/Home'
import LoanManager from './Pages/Users/MyLoans'
import MyAccountManager from './Pages/Users/MyAccount'
import ProfileManager from './Pages/Users/Profile'
import ReportManeger from './Pages/Users/Report'
import UserDashboard from './Pages/Manager/UserDashboard'
import Trunk from './Pages/Manager/Trunk'
import Loans from './Pages/Manager/Loans'
import Users from './Pages/Manager/Users'
import Reports from './Pages/Manager/Reports'
import Connections from './Pages/Manager/Connections'


function App() {
  return (
    <>
    <Router>
      <Routes>
          <Route path='' element={<LoginManager/>} />
          <Route path='/userlogin' element={<LoginUser/>} />

        <Route path='/UserDashboard' element={<UserDashboard/>}>
          <Route path='/Home' element={<HomeManager/>} />
          <Route path='/Loans' element={<LoanManager/>} />
          <Route path='/Profile' element={<ProfileManager/>} />
          <Route path='/MyAccount' element={<MyAccountManager/>} />
          <Route path='/ReportManager' element={<ReportManeger/>} />
        </Route>

        <Route path='/ManagerDashboard' element={<ManagerDashboard/>}>
          <Route path='/Trunk' element={<Trunk/>} />
          <Route path='/Loan' element={<Loans/>} />
          <Route path='/Users' element={<Users/>} />
          <Route path='/Reports' element={<Reports/>} />
          <Route path='/Connections' element={<Connections/>} />
        </Route>

       
      </Routes>
    </Router>
  </>
  )
}

export default App
